    "narrative": "The Austin Waves\u2019 offensive outlook for April 16th is anchored by **Jackson Merrill** (65.98) and **Jacob Wilson** (64.91), who represent our strongest statistical plays. **Jackson Merrill** benefits from a high-leverage spot in the three-hole against the RHP, capitalizing on a strong platoon advantage that pushes his efficiency well above his base projection. Meanwhile, **Jacob Wilson** benefits significantly from a favorable park factor and a matchup against Leiter, whose higher xERA creates a target-rich environment for **Jacob Wilson** to drive production in the middle of our order. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (60.68) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (63.81) also cleared the 60-point threshold, with **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** finding a massive 14% boost from his platoon splits against Ashcraft, making him a reliable pivot point in the second spot of the lineup.\n\nThe most difficult lineup decision today centered on **Nolan Schanuel** and **Brady House**, both of whom remained on the bench with scores of 47.95 and 47.68, respectively. While **Nolan Schanuel** looked appealing, the overall efficiency of our starting infield and utility slots proved superior, relegating him to the bench as a high-floor contingency. **Brady House** was squeezed out largely due to a difficult matchup against Ashcraft, whose ability to control the running game\u2014a 62% hold rate against base stealers\u2014dampened the appeal of a speed-focused option like **Brady House** or the even lower-ranked **Nasim Nunez** (42.25). We are keeping a close eye on **Gunnar Henderson**, whose base projection is elite, but his score has been tempered to 48.62 due to a brutal platoon disadvantage against the lefty Messick and a looming 36% rain risk that could compromise his volume today. We will monitor the weather closely, prepared to swap in **Coby Mayo** if the conditions deteriorate further or if the lineup construction shifts.",
